Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2015 16:51:37 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] ixgbe: enable DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT option

In ixgbe, the option DISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT is not enabled. AH
packets are modified in ixgbe driver. As such, these AH packets
can not pass ICV.

Suggested-by: Bruce Ashfield <bruce.ashfield@windriver.com>
Signed-off-by: Zhu Yanjun <yanjun.zhu@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/net/ixgbe/Makefile |    2 ++
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ixgbe/Makefile b/drivers/net/ixgbe/Makefile
index 326c69d..191e881 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ixgbe/Makefile
+++ b/drivers/net/ixgbe/Makefile
@@ -42,6 +42,8 @@ ixgbe-$(CONFIG_FCOE:m=y) += ixgbe_fcoe.o
 ixgbe-$(CONFIG_DEBUG_FS) += ixgbe_debugfs.o
 ixgbe-$(CONFIG_PROC_FS) += ixgbe_procfs.o
 
+EXTRA_CFLAGS += -DDISABLE_PACKET_SPLIT
+
 ifeq ($(ARCH),alpha)
   EXTRA_CFLAGS += -ffixed-8 -mno-fp-regs
 endif
